      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why though? It\u0027s irrelevant. You can do an RPC here if you want. If we were synchronizing state to some other app we would do a drop-in replacement with something that uses the network. Seems like an implementation detail irrelevant from this package\u0027s perspective to me.\n\nThe opposite is also true. I don\u0027t care if getInterface(c) produces a config.Interface which does network calls to get me the configs or if it\u0027s leveraging some local cache and the configs have already been fetched out of band, or whatever. It\u0027s all implementation detail. The only thing I care about is configs are retrieved by getInterface(c) and configs are stored by getServer(c).",
